<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-09-20T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-09-20T12:00:00-05:00" n="298" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d298">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/872: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bailly-Blanchard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port au
                                        Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-20T12:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">September 20,
                                        1919, 12 noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                    8.10 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Department’s September 18, 4 p.m.<note n="43" xml:id="d298fn43">“Cable
                                Department whether protocol has been signed and when McIlhenny will
                                leave.”</note> Full powers not yet received. McIlhenny will leave
                            immediately after signature protocol.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>